#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:26
msgid ""
"This structure represents a Fiber context `continuation <https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/Continuation>`_. The runtime does not keep references to "
"these objects, they only contain information needed to perform the context "
"switch. The switch operation updates some of the contents, however."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:30
msgid ""
"Upper limit of the C stack region. The stack grows down, so this is the "
"initial position of the stack pointer. Must be at least 16-byte aligned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:34
msgid ""
"Lower limit of the C stack region. Must be below :c:member:"
"`emscripten_fiber_t.stack_base`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:38
msgid ""
"Current position of the stack pointer. Must be between :c:member:"
"`emscripten_fiber_t.stack_base` and :c:member:`emscripten_fiber_t."
"stack_limit`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:42
msgid ""
"Entry point. If not NULL, this function will be called when the fiber is "
"switched into. Otherwise, :c:member:`emscripten_fiber_t.asyncify_data` is "
"used to rewind the call stack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:46
msgid "Opaque pointer, passed as-is to :c:member:`emscripten_fiber_t.entry`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:50
msgid ""
"Asyncify data structure. Used to unwind and rewind the call stack when "
"switching fibers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:56
msgid "Current position of the Asyncify stack pointer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:58
msgid ""
"The Asyncify stack is distinct from the C stack. It contains the call stack "
"as well as the state of WASM locals. Unlike the C stack, it grows up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:62
msgid "Upper limit of the Asyncify stack region."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:66
msgid ""
"Opaque handle to the function that needs to be called in order to rewind the "
"call stack. This value is only meaningful to the runtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:68
msgid ""
"Rewind IDs are currently thread-specific. This makes it impossible to resume "
"a fiber that has been started from a different thread."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:72
msgid "Functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:76
msgid ""
"Initializes a fiber context. It can then be entered by calling :c:func:"
"`emscripten_fiber_swap`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:78
#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:96
msgid "Pointer to the fiber structure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:79
msgid ""
"Entry point function, called when the fiber is entered for the first time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:80
msgid "Opaque pointer passed to `entry_func`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:81
msgid ""
"Pointer to memory region to use for the C stack. Must be at least 16-byte "
"aligned. This points to the lower bound of the stack, regardless of growth "
"direction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:82
msgid "Size of the C stack memory region, in bytes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:83
#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:97
msgid ""
"Pointer to memory region to use for the Asyncify stack. No special alignment "
"requirements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:84
#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:98
msgid "Size of the Asyncify stack memory region, in bytes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:86
msgid ""
"If `entry_func` returns, the entire program will end, as if `main` had "
"returned. To avoid this, you can use :c:func:`emscripten_fiber_swap` to jump "
"to another fiber."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:90
msgid ""
"Partially initializes a fiber based on the currently active context. This is "
"needed in order to switch back from a fiber into the thread's original "
"context."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:92
msgid ""
"This function sets up :c:member:`emscripten_fiber_t.stack_base` and :c:"
"member:`emscripten_fiber_t.stack_limit` to refer to the current stack "
"boundaries, sets :c:member:`emscripten_fiber_t.entry` to `NULL`, and makes :"
"c:member:`emscripten_fiber_t.asyncify_data` refer to the provided Asyncify "
"stack memory. Other fields are not changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:94
msgid ""
"Fibers initialized by this function are not complete. They are only suitable "
"to pass as the first argument to :c:func:`emscripten_fiber_swap`. Doing that "
"completes the continuation, making it possible to switch back to the "
"original context with another :c:func:`emscripten_fiber_swap`, as with a "
"normal fiber."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:102
msgid "Performs a fiber context switch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:104
msgid ""
"Fiber representing the current context. It will be partially updated, such "
"as that switching back into it via another call to :c:func:"
"`emscripten_fiber_swap` would appear to return from the original call."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/fiber.h.rst:105
msgid ""
"Fiber representing the target context. If the fiber has an entry point, it "
"will be called in the new context and set to `NULL`. Otherwise, :c:member:"
"`emscripten_fiber_t.asyncify_data` is used to rewind the call stack. If the "
"fiber is invalid or incomplete, the behavior is undefined."
msgstr ""
